task.summary: Default task
Giving some create to Financial Force despite the generally clean code.
Added tests for read access.
Renamed injecting factories into factories for clarity. (But I am still not happy with the DSL.)
Replaced interpreter pattern leveraging side effect with switch.
Renamed "fieldName" to "fieldPathString" for accuracy.
Added "this" to fieldSet instances.
Clarified and removed variables for ordering.
Added "this" to sobjectType reference.
Added "this" to enforceFlS reference.
Added "this" to sortSelectFields reference.
Added "this" to childRelationship reference. Also removed unnecessary "Schema." prefix.
Added "this" to factoryByChildRelationshipMap reference.
Extracted methods from factory to field helper class.
Changed some "public" to "private".
Reordered methods.
Created QueryInterpolationBuilder, moved relevant code into it, and consumed it.
Moved constructor towards top.
Extracted field logic to wrapepr class.
Removed unnecessary "Schemas.".
Moved Ordering list into own wrapper.
Removed unnecessary/redundant code from factory.
Added this.
Renamed collection classes and their export methods.
Limited need to export data from OrderingCollection by adding methods to it.
Moved more logic into Collections.
Renamed input parameter.
Renamed child relationship valaribles.
Created caching class for finding relationships
Modified QueryFactory to consuming caching finder instead of to repeatedly loop through relationships.
Removed unnecessary dependency.
Attempted to separate subselector.
Created clause to allow consumer to define entire where class in a single interpolation.
Renamed transaction helper to have 3rd level prefix.
Created processor for multiple DML Transactions, along with necessary interfaces and enums. The "Simple" classes should allow for simple consumption of Dml where no prerequisits are required.
First attempt at secure DML, but I'm not liking the approach much.
Converted Generic DML to use enums.
Made an interface for Generic Dml, with three concretions (with, without, and inherited sharing). Updated transaction processor to support modified Dml.
Rmoved unnecessary classes and changed unnecessary globals to public.
Started work on secure dml ... created API and security check code, but need to glue this together.
Added enum to control whether all sobjects or only first sobject should be checked.
Created class which will do checking consuming the check utilities. (WIP)
Enumerated more security possibilities.
Fixed support for inherited sharing. Refactored security configuration.
Completed security check for CRUD and FLS (untested).
Fixed integration tests.
Whitepace fixes
Changed map to use enums for keys.
Fixed bug where partial failure was not returning.
Unfixed non-bug where partial failure was not returning.
